147
00:07:08,328 --> 00:07:09,561
God...

148
00:07:09,563 --> 00:07:11,696
Guy gets stabbed;
I thought we'd have

149
00:07:11,698 --> 00:07:13,932
at least a week of peace.
Hey, Cap!

150
00:07:13,934 --> 00:07:16,668
How you doing?
Did you get my flowers?

151
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:18,636
(panting)
Captain, how
you feeling?

152
00:07:18,638 --> 00:07:20,305
Eh, five-by-five.

153
00:07:20,307 --> 00:07:23,742
Damn doc would've had me in bed
a week if I'd have let him.

154
00:07:23,744 --> 00:07:25,744
Got something for you.
Munis found a dead body

155
00:07:25,746 --> 00:07:28,346
down by the port,
throat cut from ear to ear.

156
00:07:28,348 --> 00:07:30,682
The vic's a career dirtbag,
but the work's the same.

157
00:07:30,684 --> 00:07:33,718
Uh, sir, if it's all the same,
I'd like to stay on Galavan.

158
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:35,653
It isn't.
Galavan's cooked,

159
00:07:35,655 --> 00:07:37,922
so you're back
in the rotation. What?

160
00:07:37,924 --> 00:07:40,058
I just feel like
we're missing something, sir.

161
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:42,127
There's some piece of
the puzzle that's gonna

162
00:07:42,129 --> 00:07:43,394
come back and bite us.

163
00:07:43,396 --> 00:07:45,196
Just give me a few more days.

164
00:07:45,198 --> 00:07:46,765
Answer's no.

165
00:07:46,766 --> 00:07:48,333
Be pissed, but it's
for your own good.

166
00:07:48,335 --> 00:07:50,502
Oh, and, uh...

167
00:07:50,504 --> 00:07:53,104
I'm sorry about Parks.

168
00:07:53,106 --> 00:07:54,973
She deserved better.

169
00:07:56,343 --> 00:07:57,375
BULLOCK:
Yo, Jim!

170
00:07:57,377 --> 00:07:59,511
Message from Father Mike.

171
00:07:59,513 --> 00:08:01,379
That symbol
is from something

172
00:08:01,381 --> 00:08:03,882
called the Order of St. Dumas.

173
00:08:03,884 --> 00:08:05,750
They used to have
an abbey downtown.

174
00:08:05,752 --> 00:08:08,086
Barnes just told me
to lay off of Galavan.

175
00:08:08,088 --> 00:08:10,021
Oh. Well, then
you probably don't care

176
00:08:10,023 --> 00:08:13,324
that the mayor's office tried
to buy the abbey<i> last week.</i>

177
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:15,360
Galavan tried to buy it?
Yeah.

178
00:08:15,362 --> 00:08:16,394
Some urban development nonsense.

179
00:08:16,396 --> 00:08:17,762
New owners said no.

180
00:08:17,764 --> 00:08:20,298
It's a Chinese
slap-slap joint now.

181
00:08:24,104 --> 00:08:26,271
Hell with it.
You got the address?

182
00:08:26,273 --> 00:08:28,339
Yep. Let's go get lucky.

183
00:08:31,144 --> 00:08:32,977
(knocking)

184
00:08:32,979 --> 00:08:34,979
♪ ♪

185
00:09:01,341 --> 00:09:03,341
♪ ♪

186
00:09:10,817 --> 00:09:13,351
Your uncle made me an offer:
the name of my parents' killer

187
00:09:13,353 --> 00:09:15,653
in exchange for selling him
my shares in Wayne Enterprises.

188
00:09:15,655 --> 00:09:16,988
I said no.

189
00:09:16,990 --> 00:09:18,990
But circumstances
have changed.

190
00:09:18,992 --> 00:09:21,593
You're going to sell?

191
00:09:21,595 --> 00:09:23,127
No.

192
00:09:23,129 --> 00:09:24,896
Then...
Your uncle
was arrested,

193
00:09:24,898 --> 00:09:26,364
and his assets are frozen.

194
00:09:26,366 --> 00:09:28,566
Tell him I'll pay for
his defense; in exchange,

195
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:30,668
he gives me the name.

196
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:32,737
You're taking
advantage of him.
I have something

197
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:34,772
he needs, he has something
I need, that's all.

198
00:09:34,774 --> 00:09:37,775
Do you believe what people
are saying about him?

199
00:09:37,777 --> 00:09:40,578
I don't care what people say.

200
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:42,647
My father was investigating
Wayne Enterprises,

201
00:09:42,649 --> 00:09:45,283
then he and my mother
were killed.

202
00:09:45,285 --> 00:09:47,018
Last year, I investigated
Wayne Enterprises,

203
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:48,620
and someone tried
to kill Alfred.

204
00:09:48,622 --> 00:09:50,688
Either I find out
who killed my parents

205
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:54,259
and stop whatever's happening
in my company, or I'm dead.

206
00:09:55,896 --> 00:09:57,395
I need that name.

207
00:09:57,397 --> 00:09:59,264
The grand jury
hearing is today.

208
00:09:59,266 --> 00:10:00,899
He's going to
be cleared.

209
00:10:00,901 --> 00:10:01,900
What if he's not?

210
00:10:01,902 --> 00:10:03,234
What then?

211
00:10:03,236 --> 00:10:06,304
Silver, get him
to tell you the name,

212
00:10:06,306 --> 00:10:07,672
and I will make
sure he has

213
00:10:07,674 --> 00:10:09,407
the best defense money
can buy, I promise.

214
00:10:09,409 --> 00:10:11,576
You think he's guilty.

215
00:10:11,578 --> 00:10:13,912
Why would you believe
anything he says?

216
00:10:13,914 --> 00:10:16,681
Because it would come from you.

217
00:10:18,985 --> 00:10:22,120
If you bring me the name,
I'll know it's real.

218
00:10:25,558 --> 00:10:27,558
(whispering)

219
00:10:36,136 --> 00:10:38,703
Do you mean that?

220
00:10:48,248 --> 00:10:50,448
I'll call you
after I talk to him.

221
00:10:56,890 --> 00:10:58,589
(bell tolling in distance)

222
00:11:00,393 --> 00:11:01,893
Still got to get the name.

223
00:11:01,895 --> 00:11:04,529
I will. I'm late for school.

224
00:11:15,909 --> 00:11:18,543
(crow cawing in distance)

225
00:11:19,579 --> 00:11:21,713
Not yet.

226
00:11:34,194 --> 00:11:36,194
You sure about this?

227
00:11:36,196 --> 00:11:38,629
