00:12:00,987 --> 00:12:02,820
(weak groaning)
Sir?

234
00:12:06,459 --> 00:12:07,725
(sighs)

235
00:12:08,862 --> 00:12:10,228
(grunting)

236
00:12:19,773 --> 00:12:21,672
(bones crack)

237
00:12:21,674 --> 00:12:23,841
(grunts)

238
00:12:26,179 --> 00:12:27,578
(panting)

239
00:12:33,887 --> 00:12:35,520
Stop!

240
00:12:38,224 --> 00:12:40,525
Drop the knife.

241
00:12:41,528 --> 00:12:43,895
The day of reckoning
is at hand,

242
00:12:43,897 --> 00:12:45,296
and the blood of nine

243
00:12:45,298 --> 00:12:46,998
shall wash away the sin.

244
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,132
Uh-huh.

245
00:12:48,134 --> 00:12:49,467
Who are you?

246
00:12:49,469 --> 00:12:51,102
What's your connection
to Galavan?

247
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:53,371
And Gotham shall be cleansed.

248
00:12:54,841 --> 00:12:55,840
Hey.

249
00:12:55,842 --> 00:12:56,908
(truck horn blaring)
Hey!

250
00:13:02,715 --> 00:13:04,549
GORDON:
<i>The girls at the parlor</i>

251
00:13:04,551 --> 00:13:07,652
say they saw
at least six monks.

252
00:13:07,654 --> 00:13:09,120
Uh-huh.

253
00:13:09,122 --> 00:13:12,423
They have to be a part
of this same order of St. Dumas.

254
00:13:12,425 --> 00:13:14,492
Bullock's contact says
they're penitents.

255
00:13:14,494 --> 00:13:17,728
Yeah, I forgot my
dictionary in my purse.

256
00:13:17,730 --> 00:13:21,032
They believed in
purification through pain.

257
00:13:21,034 --> 00:13:22,767
Blood.

258
00:13:22,769 --> 00:13:25,236
They were big
in the old days in Gotham.

259
00:13:25,238 --> 00:13:27,839
Then about a hundred years ago,
vanished.

260
00:13:27,841 --> 00:13:30,608
It was their crest we found
in Galavan's penthouse.

261
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:32,877
And now they're back
